<Layout title='Plasterers & Painters in Chalfont | Hancock' description='Plastering and painting in Chalfont. Fixed-price quotes from City & Guilds certified contractors covering Chalfont and the surrounding area.' activePage='areas'>
<section style="position:relative;height:340px;display:flex;align-items:flex-end;">
  <div style="position:absolute;top:0;left:0;right:0;bottom:0;background-image:url('/uploads/Hancock-plastering-and-painting%20(3).webp');background-size:cover;background-position:center 40%;"></div>
  <div style="position:absolute;top:0;left:0;right:0;bottom:0;background:linear-gradient(to top,rgba(15,23,42,0.9) 0%,rgba(15,23,42,0.45) 60%,rgba(15,23,42,0.15) 100%);"></div>
  <div style="position:relative;z-index:1;max-width:1280px;margin:0 auto;padding:0 24px 48px;width:100%;box-sizing:border-box;">
    <p style="font-size:12px;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.55);margin:0 0 12px;"><a href="/" style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.55);text-decoration:none;">Home</a> / <a href="/areas" style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.55);text-decoration:none;">Areas</a> / Chalfont</p>
    <h1 style="font-family:'Lexend',sans-serif;font-size:clamp(30px,5vw,52px);font-weight:700;color:#ffffff;margin:0 0 10px;letter-spacing:-0.04em;line-height:1.05;">Plasterer in Chalfont</h1>
    <p style="font-size:16px;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.75);margin:0;">HP8/SL9 · Plastering &amp; decorating across Chalfont St Peter and Chalfont St Giles.</p>
  </div>
</section>
<section style="padding:56px 24px;background:#ffffff;border-bottom:1px solid #E2E8F0;">
  <div style="max-width:1280px;margin:0 auto;">
    <p style="font-size:12px;font-weight:600;color:#0C7BA8;letter-spacing:0.1em;text-transform:uppercase;margin:0 0 12px;">About Chalfont</p>
    <h2 style="font-family:'Lexend',sans-serif;font-size:clamp(20px,3vw,30px);font-weight:600;color:#0F172A;margin:0 0 18px;letter-spacing:-0.03em;line-height:1.2;">Two villages with distinct characters — Chalfont St Peter is suburban; Chalfont St Giles retains a historic village centre.</h2>
    <p style="font-size:15px;color:#334155;line-height:1.75;margin:0 0 14px;">Chalfont St Peter is a commuter suburb with predominantly 1930s–70s residential. Chalfont St Giles has a genuine village character with a historic centre and older housing stock — some properties dating from the 17th and 18th centuries. Period plaster maintenance and careful work on older walls is relevant here.</p>
    <p style="font-size:15px;color:#334155;line-height:1.75;margin:0;">Typical jobs from Chalfont: renovation plastering during kitchen and extension work, exterior render on 1960s–70s semis, and period plaster refurbishment in Chalfont St Giles.</p>
  </div>
</section>
<section style="padding:56px 24px;background:#F8FAFC;border-bottom:1px solid #E2E8F0;">
  <div style="max-width:1280px;margin:0 auto;">
    <p style="font-size:12px;font-weight:600;color:#0C7BA8;letter-spacing:0.1em;text-transform:uppercase;margin:0 0 12px;">Common problems</p>
    <h2 style="font-family:'Lexend',sans-serif;font-size:clamp(20px,3vw,28px);font-weight:600;color:#0F172A;margin:0 0 28px;letter-spacing:-0.03em;">What goes wrong in Chalfont's housing stock.</h2>
    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(240px,1fr));gap:20px;">
      <div style="background:#ffffff;border:1px solid #E2E8F0;border-radius:8px;padding:24px;"><h3 style="font-family:'Lexend',sans-serif;font-size:16px;font-weight:600;color:#0F172A;margin:0 0 8px;">Render on 1960s–70s semis</h3><p style="font-size:14px;color:#334155;line-height:1.65;margin:0;">Chalfont St Peter's postwar stock carries rendered and pebble-dashed elevations that blow and craze over time, needing patch repair and repainting.</p></div>
      <div style="background:#ffffff;border:1px solid #E2E8F0;border-radius:8px;padding:24px;"><h3 style="font-family:'Lexend',sans-serif;font-size:16px;font-weight:600;color:#0F172A;margin:0 0 8px;">Very old walls in St Giles</h3><p style="font-size:14px;color:#334155;line-height:1.65;margin:0;">Chalfont St Giles has properties dating to the 17th and 18th centuries — solid walls where modern gypsum is the wrong answer and lime-compatible repair is essential.</p></div>
      <div style="background:#ffffff;border:1px solid #E2E8F0;border-radius:8px;padding:24px;"><h3 style="font-family:'Lexend',sans-serif;font-size:16px;font-weight:600;color:#0F172A;margin:0 0 8px;">Refit and extension re-skims</h3><p style="font-size:14px;color:#334155;line-height:1.65;margin:0;">Renovation and extension work across both villages leaves walls that need plastering out and re-skimming to a flat, paint-ready finish.</p></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
<section style="padding:56px 24px;background:#ffffff;border-bottom:1px solid #E2E8F0;">
  <div style="max-width:1280px;margin:0 auto;">
    <div style="display:flex;gap:64px;flex-wrap:wrap;margin-bottom:48px;">
      <div style="flex:1;min-width:300px;">
        <p style="font-size:12px;font-weight:600;color:#0C7BA8;letter-spacing:0.1em;text-transform:uppercase;margin:0 0 12px;">Neighbourhoods we work in</p>
        <h2 style="font-family:'Lexend',sans-serif;font-size:clamp(20px,3vw,28px);font-weight:600;color:#0F172A;margin:0 0 18px;letter-spacing:-0.03em;line-height:1.2;">Two villages, two characters.</h2>
        <p style="font-size:15px;color:#334155;line-height:1.75;margin:0 0 14px;"><strong>Chalfont St Peter</strong> is a commuter suburb with predominantly 1930s–70s residential and a busy village centre. <strong>Chalfont St Giles</strong> is a different proposition — a genuine historic village with a green, a conservation core, and properties dating back several centuries, including Milton's Cottage. The two need very different approaches: conventional skimming and render work in St Peter, careful period repair in St Giles.</p>
        <p style="font-size:15px;color:#334155;line-height:1.75;margin:0;">Both sit in the Buckinghamshire Green Belt with an affluent, settled population.</p>
      </div>
      <div style="flex:1;min-width:300px;">
        <p style="font-size:12px;font-weight:600;color:#0C7BA8;letter-spacing:0.1em;text-transform:uppercase;margin:0 0 12px;">What homeowners ask for</p>
        <h2 style="font-family:'Lexend',sans-serif;font-size:clamp(20px,3vw,28px);font-weight:600;color:#0F172A;margin:0 0 18px;letter-spacing:-0.03em;line-height:1.2;">Plastering, rendering, and period repair.</h2>
        <p style="font-size:15px;color:#334155;line-height:1.75;margin:0 0 14px;">Renovation plastering during kitchen and extension work, exterior render on the postwar semis, and period plaster refurbishment in St Giles. Quality interior decorating runs throughout. Exterior work is scheduled for the drier months.</p>
        <p style="font-size:15px;color:#334155;line-height:1.75;margin:0;">Considered budgets, careful work, fixed price up front.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p style="font-size:12px;font-weight:600;color:#0C7BA8;letter-spacing:0.1em;text-transform:uppercase;margin:0 0 24px;">Working in Chalfont</p>
    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(220px,1fr));gap:20px;">
      <div><h3 style="font-family:'Lexend',sans-serif;font-size:15px;font-weight:600;color:#0F172A;margin:0 0 8px;">~18 minutes from base</h3><p style="font-size:14px;color:#334155;line-height:1.65;margin:0;">A short run from Harefield via Denham. A regular working area, with Gerrards Cross and Amersham on the same routes.</p></div>
      <div><h3 style="font-family:'Lexend',sans-serif;font-size:15px;font-weight:600;color:#0F172A;margin:0 0 8px;">Period-aware</h3><p style="font-size:14px;color:#334155;line-height:1.65;margin:0;">St Giles's centuries-old walls get breathable, lime-compatible repair. We assess construction before specifying.</p></div>
      <div><h3 style="font-family:'Lexend',sans-serif;font-size:15px;font-weight:600;color:#0F172A;margin:0 0 8px;">Access &amp; parking</h3><p style="font-size:14px;color:#334155;line-height:1.65;margin:0;">Suburban St Peter is simple; the St Giles village lanes we plan loading around to avoid disruption.</p></div>
      <div><h3 style="font-family:'Lexend',sans-serif;font-size:15px;font-weight:600;color:#0F172A;margin:0 0 8px;">Clean, tidy, insured</h3><p style="font-size:14px;color:#334155;line-height:1.65;margin:0;">Surfaces and features protected, site left tidy daily. Fully insured, City &amp; Guilds qualified, no subcontractors.</p></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
